{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"One of the biggest challenges in computer graphics"},{"time":3000,"text":"has been being able to create a photo-real,"},{"time":5000,"text":"digital human face."},{"time":7000,"text":"And one of the reasons it is so difficult is that, unlike aliens and dinosaurs,"},{"time":10000,"text":"we look at human faces every day."},{"time":13000,"text":"They are very important to how we communicate with each other."},{"time":15000,"text":"As a result, we're tuned in to the subtlest things"},{"time":18000,"text":"that could possibly be wrong with a computer rendering,"},{"time":20000,"text":"in order to believe whether these things are realistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"And what I'm going to do in the next five minutes"},{"time":25000,"text":"is take you through a process"},{"time":27000,"text":"where we tried to create a reasonably photo-realistic computer-generated face,"},{"time":30000,"text":"using some computer graphics technology we've developed,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and also some collaborators at a company called Image Metrics."},{"time":35000,"text":"And we're going to try to do a photo-real face"},{"time":37000,"text":"of an actress named Emily O'Brien, who is right there."},{"time":40000,"text":"And that's actually a completely computer-generated rendering of her face."},{"time":43000,"text":"By the end of the talk, we're going to see it move."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"The way that we did this is we tried to start with Emily herself,"},{"time":48000,"text":"who was gracious enough to come to our laboratory"},{"time":51000,"text":"in Marina Del Rey, and sit for a session in Light Stage 5."},{"time":54000,"text":"This is a face-scanning sphere, with 156 white LEDs all around"},{"time":58000,"text":"that allow us to photograph her"},{"time":60000,"text":"in a series of very controlled illumination conditions."},{"time":63000,"text":"And the lighting that we use these days looks something like this."},{"time":66000,"text":"We shoot all of these photographs in about three seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"And we basically capture enough information"},{"time":71000,"text":"with video projector patterns that drape over the contours of her face,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and different principle directions of light from the light stage,"},{"time":77000,"text":"to figure out both the coarse-scale"},{"time":79000,"text":"and the fine-scale detail of her face."},{"time":81000,"text":"If we zoom in on this photograph right here,"},{"time":83000,"text":"we can see it's a really nice photograph to have of her,"},{"time":85000,"text":"because she is lit from absolutely everywhere at the same time"},{"time":89000,"text":"to get a nice image of her facial texture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"And in addition, we've actually used polarizers on all the lights --"},{"time":94000,"text":"just like polarized sunglasses can block"},{"time":96000,"text":"the glare off of the road,"},{"time":98000,"text":"polarizers can block the shine off of the skin,"},{"time":100000,"text":"so we don't get all those specular reflections to take this map."},{"time":103000,"text":"Now, if we turn the polarizers around just a little bit,"},{"time":105000,"text":"we can actually bring that specular reflection"},{"time":107000,"text":"of the skin back in,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and you can see she looks kind of shiny and oily at this point."},{"time":112000,"text":"If you take the difference between these two images here,"},{"time":115000,"text":"you can get an image lit from the entire sphere of light"},{"time":117000,"text":"of just the shine off of Emily's skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"I don't think any photograph like this had ever been taken"},{"time":122000,"text":"before we had done this."},{"time":124000,"text":"And this is very important light to capture,"},{"time":127000,"text":"because this is the light that reflects off the first surface of the skin."},{"time":129000,"text":"It doesn't get underneath the translucent"},{"time":131000,"text":"layers of the skin and blur out."},{"time":133000,"text":"And, as a result, it's a very good cue"},{"time":135000,"text":"to the detailed shape of the skin-pore structure"},{"time":138000,"text":"and all of the fine wrinkles that all of us have,"},{"time":140000,"text":"the things that actually make us look like real humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"So, if we use information that comes off of this specular reflection,"},{"time":146000,"text":"we can go from a traditional face scan"},{"time":148000,"text":"that might have the gross contours of the face and the basic shape,"},{"time":152000,"text":"and augment it with information"},{"time":154000,"text":"that puts in all of that skin pore structure and fine wrinkles."},{"time":157000,"text":"And, even more importantly,"},{"time":159000,"text":"since this is a photometric process that only takes three seconds to capture,"},{"time":162000,"text":"we can shoot Emily"},{"time":164000,"text":"in just part of an afternoon,"},{"time":166000,"text":"in many different facial poses and facial expressions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"So, here you can see her moving her eyes around, moving her mouth around."},{"time":172000,"text":"And these we're actually going to use to create a photo-real digital character."},{"time":175000,"text":"If you take a look at these scans that we have of Emily,"},{"time":179000,"text":"you can see that the human face does an enormous amount of amazing things"},{"time":182000,"text":"as it goes into different facial expressions."},{"time":185000,"text":"You can see things. Not only the face shape changes,"},{"time":188000,"text":"but all sorts of different skin buckling and skin wrinkling occurs."},{"time":192000,"text":"You can see that the skin pore structure changes enormously"},{"time":196000,"text":"from stretched skin pores"},{"time":198000,"text":"to the regular skin texture."},{"time":200000,"text":"You can see the furrows in the brow and how the microstructure changes there."},{"time":203000,"text":"You can see muscles pulling down at flesh to bring her eyebrows down."},{"time":207000,"text":"Her muscles bulging in her forehead when she winces like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"In addition to this kind of high-resolution geometry,"},{"time":213000,"text":"since it's all captured with cameras, we've got a great texture map to use for the face."},{"time":217000,"text":"And by looking at how the different color channels of the illumination,"},{"time":219000,"text":"the red and the green and the blue,"},{"time":221000,"text":"diffuse the light differently,"},{"time":223000,"text":"we can come up with a way of shading the skin on the computer."},{"time":226000,"text":"Then, instead of looking like a plaster mannequin,"},{"time":229000,"text":"it actually looks like it's made out of living human flesh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"And this is what we used"},{"time":234000,"text":"to give to the company Image Metrics"},{"time":236000,"text":"to create a rigged, digital version of Emily."},{"time":239000,"text":"We're just seeing the coarse-scale geometry here."},{"time":241000,"text":"But they basically created a digital puppet of her,"},{"time":244000,"text":"where you can pull on these various strings,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and it actually moves her face in ways that are"},{"time":248000,"text":"completely consistent with the scans that we took."},{"time":250000,"text":"And, in addition to the coarse-scale geometry,"},{"time":252000,"text":"they also used all of that detail"},{"time":254000,"text":"to create a set of what are called \"displacement maps\""},{"time":257000,"text":"that animate as well."},{"time":260000,"text":"These are the displacement maps here."},{"time":262000,"text":"And you can see those different wrinkles actually show up as she animates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"So the next process was then to animate her."},{"time":267000,"text":"We actually used one of her own performances to provide the source data."},{"time":271000,"text":"So, by analyzing this video with computer vision techniques,"},{"time":274000,"text":"they were able to drive the facial rig"},{"time":276000,"text":"with the computer-generated performance."},{"time":278000,"text":"So what you're going to see now, after this,"},{"time":280000,"text":"is a completely photo-real digital face."},{"time":282000,"text":"We can turn the volume up a little bit if that's available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"Emily: Image Metrics is a markerless, performance-driven animation company."},{"time":288000,"text":"We specialize in high-quality facial animation"},{"time":291000,"text":"for video games and films."},{"time":293000,"text":"Image Metrics is a markerless, performance-driven animation company."},{"time":297000,"text":"We specialize in high quality facial animation"},{"time":300000,"text":"for video games and films."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"Paul Debevec: So, if we break that down into layers, here's that diffuse component"},{"time":305000,"text":"we saw in the first slide."},{"time":307000,"text":"Here is the specular component animating."},{"time":309000,"text":"You can see all the wrinkles happening there."},{"time":311000,"text":"And there is the underlying wireframe mesh."},{"time":316000,"text":"And that is Emily herself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"Now, where are we going with this here?"},{"time":320000,"text":"We've gone a little bit beyond Light Stage 5. This is Light Stage 6,"},{"time":324000,"text":"and we're looking at taking this technology"},{"time":326000,"text":"and applying it to whole human bodies."},{"time":328000,"text":"This is Bruce Lawmen, one of our researchers in the group,"},{"time":330000,"text":"who graciously agreed to get captured running in the Light Stage."},{"time":333000,"text":"And let's take a look at a computer-generated version"},{"time":335000,"text":"of Bruce, running in a new environment."},{"time":343000,"text":"And thank you very much."},{"time":345000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}